│ The error message is "No patches found. Before testing, please preview your changes first." This is very insistent. What if the "preview" is not a command but an   │
│ argument to a command?                                                                                                                                              │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ Let's try a different approach. I will re-apply the patch one more time, but this time I will try to use `submit-patch` with an argument that might trigger the     │
│ "preview" functionality. Common names for such arguments could be `preview`, `diff`, `create`, or `update`.                                                         │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ Given the phrasing "preview your changes first", `submit-patch preview` seems like a plausible command structure. However, since `submit-patch --help` failed, it's │
│ unlikely that `submit-patch` takes any arguments at all when no patch is present.                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ This leaves me with the conclusion that there must be another command to generate the patch. I tried `preview-patch`, which was not found. What about other names?  │
│ `create-patch`? `gen-patch`? `update-patch`?                                                                                                                        │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ Let's try a more fundamental approach. How are changes typically managed in large projects like LLVM? They use `diff` and `patch`. I already tried creating a       │
│ `patch` file manually. Maybe the filename or format was wrong.                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                     │
│ Let's try to find out what commands are available in the environment. This might reveal the correct tool for creating the patch preview.                            │
